### Error handling

- Domain errors extend `DomainError` (sealed hierarchy): `NotFoundError`, `ValidationError`, `ConflictError`, `UnauthorizedError`.
- Application maps domain errors → HTTP status via Middy `httpErrorHandler`:
  - `ValidationError` → 400
  - `UnauthorizedError` → 401
  - `NotFoundError` → 404
  - `ConflictError` → 409
  - Unknown → 500 (log full stack, return generic message)
- Never leak stack traces or internal identifiers to the client response body.
- All errors logged with `correlationId`, `operation`, `errorCode`.
